    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-04-04T03:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-04-04T03:25:00-05:00" n="55"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/4036: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-04-04T11:00:00+02:35"
                            >April 4, 1936—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>198. My 197, April 4, 8 a.m. I now learn four natives were accidentally killed
                    and a number wounded by stray bullets promiscuously fired at the planes by
                    soldiers and civilians. Many natives and some foreigners are making preparations
                    to leave the city and hide in the neighboring countryside.</p>
                <p>American colony very calm and has been most helpful to me in connection with
                    certain precautions in the event of a more serious raid.</p>
                <p>It is unofficially reported that Jig Jiga was again bombed this morning and that
                    three Italian planes flew over Diré Dawa but without dropping bombs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
